      "rationale": "A three-level mesh refinement study was conducted (coarse: 2.1M cells, medium: 5.8M cells, fine: 14.3M cells). Richardson extrapolation yielded GCI values below 3.2% for the normalized index of hemolysis at all five operating conditions. The medium mesh was selected as the production mesh, providing adequate accuracy with acceptable computational cost."
