      "rationale": "Validation experiments were conducted under controlled laboratory conditions matching the five target flow-speed combinations (2–6 L/min, 2000–3500 RPM). Temperature, fluid viscosity, and inlet pressure boundary conditions were recorded and confirmed within ±5% of target values. Test conditions are judged representative of the COU operating envelope."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "CFD-predicted hemolysis index values fall within experimental uncertainty bounds at all five operating points.",
      "rationale": "Predicted normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) values were compared against experimental measurements from the FDA benchmark dataset. At all five operating points, CFD predictions fell within the expanded experimental uncertainty (k=2) of the measured NIH values. The relative hemolysis index RH < 1 criterion was satisfied for the worst-case condition."
    },
    {
