      "acceptanceCriteria": "The QoIs used in validation (NIH, RH) are directly relevant to the clinical decision being supported.",
      "rationale": "The normalized index of hemolysis and relative hemolysis index are the accepted industry metrics for pump-induced blood damage assessment. These QoIs are directly mapped to the regulatory acceptance criterion (RH < 1 relative to predicate device) and are clinically meaningful for CPB device evaluation."
