    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "rationale": "A comprehensive qualitative assessment of model form adequacy was conducted by the simulation team in consultation with subject-matter experts in computational hemodynamics. The SST k-omega turbulence model was selected based on its established performance in rotating machinery flows with adverse pressure gradients, and the power-law hemolysis damage model (Giersiepen-Wurzinger correlation) was chosen for its widespread regulatory acceptance in blood pump CFD submissions. Literature benchmarking against five independent pump geometries confirmed that the model form captures the dominant physics of pump-induced hemolysis at the shear stress magnitudes and exposure times relevant to CPB operation. The team concluded that the selected model form is appropriate for the intended COU, with no systematic bias identified that would invalidate the RH < 1 acceptance criterion under worst-case operating conditions. This qualitative evaluation, supported by the breadth of published validation evidence for this model class, provides sufficient confidence in model form adequacy for MRL 2 classification."
    },
